<AnchorPane prefHeight="480.0" prefWidth="448.0" stylesheets="@red-theme.css" xmlns="http://javafx.com/javafx/8.0.111" xmlns:fx="http://javafx.com/fxml/1" fx:controller="application.view.InstructionWindowController">
   <children>
      <Label layoutX="115.0" layoutY="35.0" styleClass="title" text="Instructions" />
      <TextArea editable="false" layoutX="15.0" layoutY="75.0" prefHeight="320.0" prefWidth="420.0" text="Welcome to Taatai. Taatai is an app for practicing to pronounce Maori numbers.&#10;&#10;Play&#10;Pressing the Play button will prompt you to select a game mode. There are three to choose from: &quot;Equation&quot;, &quot;Number&quot; and &quot;Practice&quot;.&#10;&#10;Number Mode&#10;In Number mode, you are tested on your pronunciation of Maori Numbers and given a score out of 10. There are 2 difficulties in Number Mode: Easy and Hard. In Easy mode, you are only tested on numbers below 10, but in Hard mode, you can be tested on any number below 100. Your statistics and progress are saved in this mode.&#10;&#10;Equation Mode&#10;In Equation mode, you are asked to choose up to 4 maths operators are given 10 simple maths equations based on the operators selected. You then solve these equations one-by-one by speaking your answer in Maori. After all 10 are completed, you will be given a score out of 10. There are 2 difficulties in Number Mode: Easy and Hard. In Easy mode, you are only tested on numbers below 10, but in Hard mode, you can be tested on any number below 100. Your statistics and progress are saved in this mode.&#10;&#10;Training Mode&#10;In Training mode, you can choose which numbers you would like to pronounce, and practice them. Your stats will not be saved in this mode.&#10;&#10;Statistics&#10;In the statistics window, you can view your statistics for any given date which you played on. Your statistics will show you which questions you attempted on the date chosen, as well as whether or not you got it correct or incorrect.&#10;&#10;Switch User&#10;The Switch User button takes you back to the Login window, where you can Change the current User.&#10;&#10;" wrapText="true" AnchorPane.leftAnchor="14.0" AnchorPane.rightAnchor="14.0" />
      <JFXButton layoutX="174.0" layoutY="410.0" onAction="#handleMainMenuBtn" styleClass="default-btn" text="Ok, got it!" />
   </children>
